a unique work with a message for us in today 's world this is the first volume of churchill 's noble prize winning six part chronicle of world war ii . the gathering storm depicts the rise of hitler and the indifference of the leaders of the european democracies to the clouds of the gathering storm . churchill incorporates contemporary documentation and his own reminiscence in this opening memoir . churchill was a great statesman with great literary ability - a winning combination . the gathering storm a unique work and has a message for us in today 's world . read and reviewed by jimmie a. keple